data.name: Barrett Key Farm
data.seo_description: The Barrett Key farm is a 222-acre Cotton and Soybean farm located 7 miles north of Kennett, Missouri in Dunklin County, Missouri. The "Bootheel" region of southeastern Missouri is known for its lighter soils and superb groundwater access.

data.name: Pine City Farm
data.seo_description: Learn about our latest offering, the Pine City Farm, a 181 acre cotton and soybean farm in Dunklin County, Missouri. Located 2 miles south of Holcomb, MO. The farm consists of 3 tracts approximately 4 miles apart.

data.name: Tenmile Peanut Farm - South
data.seo_description: Located in the heart of the largest peanut growing region in the country, this farm contains 179 acres of irrigated and dry crop ground. The farm's loamy-sand soil is highly suitable for peanut production, but also has supported cotton and melon crops in previous seasons.
